data.content:
**No Thread.Abort migration needed.** Your code does not use `Thread.Abort`, `ThreadAbortException`, `Thread.ResetAbort`, or `Thread.Interrupt`. It only uses `Thread.Start`, `Thread.Join`, and `Thread.Sleep` — all of which work identically in .NET 8.

This code will compile and run correctly as-is on `net8.0`.

**Optional modernization** (unrelated to Thread.Abort):

You could replace manual `Thread` management with `Parallel.ForEach` or `Task.Run` for cleaner code:

```csharp
public async Task RunBatchAsync(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    await Parallel.ForEachAsync(items, async (item, ct) =>
    {
        await Task.Delay(100, ct); // replaces Thread.Sleep
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    });
}
```

This is purely a modernization suggestion — your existing code requires zero changes to migrate to .NET 8.
